race.comment: ENAMORADA (7) resumes, looking to keep her unbeaten record intact. She bolted in on debut at Ballarat, heavily supported and too good again here in a BM66 before a break. She's since been sold and transferred to Ciaron Maher (ex-Gavin Bedggood) and profiles as a horse who will be winning much stronger races than this. ATTACHMENTS (3) is a handy mare who won well at Kilmore two back, not far away in this grade when last seen at Sandown Lakeside. She'll take holding out. ULTRA BLUE (6) won a Class 1 second up at Geelong, getting the right run on speed there. He should be fitter again and gets the right map to measure up. RUSSIAN FRONT (10) is consistent and has place claims.
